  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Defining the Objective**\n\nOkay, I\'m now clear on the user\'s objective. I understand they need a Spanish scheduling app to build work schedules. I\'m focusing on feature breakdown, including the need for \"blocks\" to differentiate roles or shifts, which I see as a key organizational feature. I\'m working on a design that reflects this.\n\n\n**Refining Calculations & Schedule**\n\nI\'m now calculating total hours per day and week. The scheduling logic will cover a full week (Monday-Sunday) to ensure flexibility, even though the provided timeframe was \"Friday to Sunday\". I need to figure out how to incorporate these time spans (which are not standard) into the Spanish work schedule.\n\n\n**Calculating Costs and Entities**\n\nI\'m now diving into the calculations and the data structures. I\'ll focus on weekly cost calculation and handling overnight shifts (22:00 to 06:00, etc.). I\'ll define \"Employee,\" \"Category,\" and \"Shift\" entities, including IDs, hourly rates, and color-coding for shifts. I\'ll need to figure out how to incorporate these time spans (which are not standard) into the Spanish work schedule.\n\n\n**Planning the UI & Implementation**\n\nI\'m now outlining the UI layout. I\'ll have staff/category management at the top, a schedule grid in the middle displaying shifts for employees, and summaries at the bottom, which will show total hours, pay, and costs. I\'ve broken down the implementation into six steps, starting with type definitions and culminating in state management.\n\n\n**Simplifying State Management**\n\nI\'ve decided to keep state management straightforward, either using standard React state within `App.tsx` or a custom `useSchedule` hook to pass data down. I\'m focusing now on adding metadata in `metadata.json` and installing necessary libraries, if any. I\'m choosing to write helper functions for time math instead of using a library like `date-fns`, as it\'s simple enough to calculate with `HH:mm` parsing. I\'m drafting a helper `calculateHours` function to determine time calculations.\n\nI\'m starting on the schedule grid itself. The basic layout will be a table, with days (Monday to Sunday) as headers, employee rows, and cells representing shifts. Clicking an empty cell will open a modal to add a shift.\n\n\n**Clarifying Schedule Dates**\n\nI\'m now clarifying the date range and calendar layout. While the user\'s phrasing, \"dise\303\261ar de viernes a domingo,\" might suggest a Friday-Sunday timeframe, I\'ll build a standard seven-day calendar for maximum flexibility, from Monday to Sunday, to be extra robust.\n\n**Defining Dependencies & Strategy**\n\nI\'ve determined I need dependencies: `lucide-react`, `clsx`, and `tailwind-merge`. I\'m creating a file structure. It\'ll include types, utility functions for time, managers for employees and categories, the schedule grid, the totals dashboard, and the main application component. Finally, I\'ve got to ensure the Spanish terminology is correct, for example: Categor\303\255as, Empleados, Horario, etc.\n\n\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 19
      nanos: 410270700
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
